    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-27T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-27T16:00:00-05:00" n="650"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/9–2751: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Canada</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Woodward</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ottawa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-27T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 27, 1951—5 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. Ottawa officials handling govt problems seriously disturbed by reports Belg
                    imposing restrictions discriminatory against dollar imports. Initial reaction
                    strongly against approval of <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss> waiver.
                    Canadians do not yet know, however, extent to which their trade directly
                    affected. Reports from Canadian sources Geneva and Brussels leave doubt whether
                    restrictions already in effect or contemplated. Canadian officials, emphasize
                    Belg over balance of payments situation excellent and by <gloss
                        target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss> standards discrimination unjustified.
                    Instructions to Canadian del Geneva probably will be sent after
                    interdepartmental mtg October 2 at DepMin level.</p>
                <p>Canadians critical encouragement by <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> of Belg
                    restrictions as reported by Hoffman <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi> Sept
                    23 page 26. They have in past voiced misgivings repeatedly to <gloss
                        target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss> and others in Washington that <gloss
                        target="#t_EPU1">EPU</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> wld
                    lead to discriminatory restrictions.</p>
                <p>Pls inform <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> by telephone what US position is
                    and whether Hoffman report accurate.</p>
                <p>Dept pass Geneva; sent Dept 53, rptd Geneva unnumbered for <gloss
                        target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodward</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
